Just a general comment for the thread , the proper way to handle this behavior is not to use window.location at all. Just add a line in your try block: 
     setDescription(" "); 
This sets the value of description back to undefined, clearing the text input.  When you change the state in React it also re-renders just that component (rather than the whole page) which is the desired behavior. Here we already have a preventDefault() to keep a full page refresh from happening and he went and added one back in.

